This paper discusses domain adaptation, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on machine learning and the adaptation of algorithms to new data distributions, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses practical applications in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also touches on the topic of subspace mapping, which is related to signal processing (cs.SD).
